<SECOND>PM-Box Office,0451</SECOND>
<HEAD>`Major League' Leads Off In First Place</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN HORN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 `` Major League,'' the story of a big-league baseball team inherited by a showgirl, hit a home run in its first time at bat at the nation's box offices. The Paramount movie starring <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Berenger </PERSON> as a washed-up catcher on the team took in $ 8 million last weekend to finish at the top of the box office rankings by <ORGANIZATION> Exhibitor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. Three other new releases finished among the top six movies last weekend Universal's `` The <ORGANIZATION> Dream </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Team </ORGANIZATION>,'' a comedy about four mental patients in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, debutted in second place with $ 5.7 million. `` Rain Man,'' winner of four top Oscars, continued its strong post Academy Awards-showing by gathering $ 4.1 million to finish in third place. Another newcomer, `` Cyborg,'' starring <PERSON> Jean-Claude </PERSON> <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Damme </PERSON> as `` the first hero of the 21st century,'' finished fourth on receipts of $ 3.1 million. `` Fletch Lives,'' a comedy sequel featuring <LOCATION> Chevy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Chase </LOCATION>, landed in fifth with $ 2.6 million. Next was `` Dead Calm,'' a new thriller set on a sailboat, with sales of $ 2.4 million. In seventh was the re-release of `` The Rescuers,'' with $ 1.7 million. `` Lean on Me,'' the dramatization of the life of high school principal <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Clark </PERSON>, finished in eighth with $ 1.5 million. Completing the top 10 were the comedy `` Bill and <PERSON> Ted </PERSON>'s Excellent Adventure,'' with $ 1.4 million and the bedroom drama `` Dangerous Liaisons,'' with $ 1.1 million. Here are the top movies for last weekend as tallied by Exhibitor Relations, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater screens, average per screen, total gross and number of weeks in release. 1. `` Major League,'' Paramount, $ 8.8 million, 1,541 screens, $ 5,734 per screen, $ 8.8 million, one week. 2. `` Dream Team,'' Universal, $ 5.7 million, 1,316 screens, $ 4,335 per screen, $ 5.7 million, one week. 3. `` Rain Man,'' <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Artists </ORGANIZATION>, $ 4.1 million, 1,580 screens, $ 2,604 per screen, $ 148.6 million, 16 weeks. 4. `` Cyborg,'' Cannon, $ 3.1 million, 830 screens, $ 3,831 per screen, $ 3.1 million, one week. 5. `` Fletch Lives,'' Universal, $ 2.6 million, 1,473 screens, $ 1,770 per screen, $ 27.2 million, three weeks. 6. `` Dead Calm,'' <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bros. </ORGANIZATION>, $ 2.4 million, 959 screens, $ 2,569 per screen, $ 2.4 million, one week. 7. `` The Rescuers,'' <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION>, $ 1.7 million, 1,463 screens, $ 1,172 per screen, $ 16.2 million, four weeks. 8. `` Lean on Me,'' <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bros. </ORGANIZATION>, $ 1.5 million, 904 screens, $ 1,703 per screen, $ 25.9 million, five weeks. 9. `` Bill and <PERSON> Ted </PERSON>'s Excellent Adventure,'' <ORGANIZATION> Orion </ORGANIZATION>, $ 1.4 million, 1,201 screens, $ 1,171 per screen, $ 33.7 million, seven weeks. 10. `` Dangerous Liaisons,'' <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bros. </ORGANIZATION>, $ 1.1 million, 622 screens, $ 1,788 per screen, $ 29.2 million, 15 weeks.
