upervisory force for a transition period during which elections would be held. On Friday, <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> said <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s proposal was `` inappropriate, as usual.'' Monday's <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> statement reiterated calls for an international peace conference on the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> involving all parties concerned, `` including the Palestinian state'' proclaimed Nov. 15 by the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION>, which acts as the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> legislature. It is the first <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> mention of the Palestinian state as the representative of Palestinians at an international forum. Previous references have been to the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> itself.
