alled the fire department,'' said the man, who declined to provide his name. On March 4, 1988, another twin-engine <ORGANIZATION> Fokker </ORGANIZATION> 27 en route from <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> to <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> crashed in the countryside, killing 23 people. The final report from that investigation provided no reason for the crash.
