>, who has been a commercial fisherman 26 years. `` Everybody is worried what the long-term effect is. Depending on the long-term effects, it can mean your way of life is gone as a fisherman. `` It could be bad. It really could. Then, it might not be. It could affect everybody here. This is a fishing village and everything is tied to that.'' <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Eoff </PERSON> said he thinks cleanup officials should attack the oil before its coats <LOCATION> Kodiak </LOCATION>'s rocky coastline. `` I feel they better do everything they can, including hiring local boats and people, and get them out there.'' But he said that may not be enough. `` In the long term, who knows? It could be years, and years and years and years of dead areas.''
