<DATELINE>BRANDON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Marsman </PERSON> and <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Christiansen </PERSON> live half a world apart, but <PERSON> Christiansen </PERSON> has given the younger man a link to the father he never knew, an aviator shot down over <LOCATION> Indonesia </LOCATION> in World War II. <PERSON> Christiansen </PERSON> had carried a wedding band belonging to <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Marsman </PERSON>, an aviator in the <ORGANIZATION> Dutch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION>, since the ring was given to him by natives on an <LOCATION> Indonesian </LOCATION> island in 1945. `` I kept that ring all these years thinking that some day, somewhere we would find <PERSON> Marsman </PERSON>'s widow,'' <PERSON> Christiansen </PERSON> said in a telephone interview from his home in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Wales </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>. `` All we had to go on was the name ` <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON>' that was on the inside of the ring.'' With the help of members of <PERSON> Marsman </PERSON>'s old 18th Squadron and a lot of luck, <PERSON> Christiansen </PERSON> finally made contact with the family in <LOCATION> Brandon </LOCATION> in 1987. The retired major mailed the ring to the <PERSON> Marsman </PERSON> family and later traveled to <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> to visit the flier's widow and son. `` Completing this has been one of the highlights of my life,'' said <PERSON> Christiansen </PERSON>. `` There's no way to tell you what this has meant to me,'' <PERSON> Marsman </PERSON> said. `` I was two weeks old when his <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> bomber went down and all I knew from childhood was that he was missing in action and that's all my mother ever knew.'' <PERSON> Christiansen </PERSON> said his unit was assigned to sweep through <LOCATION> Kai </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION> in search of lingering Japa