<HEAD>Ford Recalls 340,000 Trucks and Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> has recalled more than 340,000 cars and trucks for safety-related and other problems. The company said Monday it was asking owners of 26,000 1988-89 F-Super Duty trucks and truck chassis to return the vehicles because of front-end suspension problems that could cause shaking and loss of steering control. <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> said a bolt attaching the front axle track bar bracket to the front cross-member may loosen. The company said it was aware of about 120 cases of front-end `` shimmy,'' but no injuries because of it. The company also said 750 of its 1989 <ORGANIZATION> Lincoln </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> cars were being recalled to tighten a bolt in a rear seat-belt attachment. Those cars were assembled between late November and early December last year. In a non-safety-related matter, <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> said it was asking 302,000 owners if some 1988 <PERSON> Lincoln </PERSON> <PERSON> Continentals </PERSON>, Mercury Sables and <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> Taurus cars and some F-Series trucks and Econoline vans to return their vehicles for alternator inspections. The company said a problem with an epoxy bond could cause electrical system problems. <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> also said it would provide coverage for about 12,500 1985-86 Merkur XR4Ti cars with leather interiors. The upholstery may harden, crack or discolor and the seams may fail, the company said. Owners of all vehicles involved in the four announcements will have repairs performed free of charge.
