<HEAD>London Stocks Decline in Early Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices slipped in early trading Tuesday but regained some ground as bargain hunters moved into the market. Dealers said prices initially declined on mounting interest rate fears and concerns over the general health of the British economy. However, some market watchers said a handful of institutions could not resist picking up some selected issues once the <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times-Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> 100-stock index approached the 2,000-point level. Several market makers also said a strong performance by the British pound kept fears of imminent interest rate hikes at bay. The firmer pound gave the market renewed confidence, one market maker suggested. At midday, the FT-SE index was off 5.5 points, or 0.2 percent, at 2,019.5. Earlier, the index was down more than 23 points. Volume amounted to a modest 322.7 million shares by midday, compared with 257.7 million shares at the same time Monday.
