<HEAD>Southwest Airlines Report Features Punch-Out Fun</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN A. BOLT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 In addition to the facts and figures formally found in a firm's annual report, <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> 1988 features fun, in the form of a paper airplane. `` This was one of those wonderful years when we made a lot of money and it seemed to be we made a lot of money by getting back to the basics. ... and we translated that to what we thought was the most basic of all airplanes, the paper airplane,'' said <PERSON> Tim </PERSON> <PERSON> McClure </PERSON>, executive creative director of <LOCATION> Austin </LOCATION> advertising agency <ORGANIZATION> GSD </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; M, which designed the report. The booklet, besides reporting on <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION>'s record $ 57.95 million in profit, traces the construction of a paper airplane from the first folding of the paper to the final painting to resemble Shamu One, <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION>'s `` flying whale'' jet rolled out last year during the airline's promotion of <ORGANIZATION> Sea </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> theme parks in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>. `` You think every pre-schooler and first grader in <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> will want one?'' asked <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Charlotte </PERSON> <PERSON> Goddard </PERSON>. `` Or all the CEOs?'' Besides a picture of Chairman <PERSON> Herb </PERSON> <PERSON> Kelleher </PERSON> throwing a paper airplane, the middle of the report features a four-page foldout picture of Shamu One. On the back page, there's the punch-out version of the unusually painted plane, with assembly instructions and this `` helpful hint:'' `` <PERSON> Herb </PERSON> attaches a paper clip to the nose for longer flights -LRB- Shamu One's, not his -RRB-.'' Even though <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATIO